caption: I ordered from them for the first time. It was through UberEats. The menu on there is wrong. It said turkey bacon was a topping option, but when I got my pizza, regular bacon was on it. It could’ve been a disaster if I didn’t know the difference. I’m allergic to pork, so I could’ve had a reaction due to their false claim. And if I wasn’t supposed to eat pork for religious reasons, that would also be an issue. I tried calling the restaurant to have them correct the mistake, but they never answered. I wasted $7.  On another note, I did not like the pizza very much. The cheese was very sparse and the toppings were all in the middle. Edges of the jumbo slice were pretty much bare crust and sauce.
